  "issue_title": "[BUG] Cache fallback uses stale evaluation when miner legitimately has zero PRs",
  "issue_body": "## Description\n\n`store_or_use_cached_evaluation` currently falls back to cached data whenever `total_prs == 0`.  \nThis treats two different states as the same:\n\n1. GitHub PR fetch failed (fallback is desirable)\n2. GitHub fetch succeeded but miner truly has no current PRs (fallback is incorrect)\n\nBecause `load_miners_prs` does not expose a fetch-failure signal, stale cached evaluations can be reused for inactive/zero-PR miners.\n\n## Steps to Reproduce\n\n1. Cache a prior successful evaluation for a UID with merged PRs.\n2. Run a later scoring round for the same UID where GitHub returns a valid empty PR list (`nodes: []`).\n3. Observe that the validator replaces the current zero-PR evaluation with cached data.\n\n## Expected Behavior\n\nCache fallback should happen only when GitHub PR fetching fails/unavailable, not when a miner legitimately has zero PRs.\n\n## Actual Behavior\n\nA valid zero-PR result is treated like a fetch failure, causing stale cached contributions/scores to be reused.\n\n## Environment\n\n- OS: Linux (local + CI `ubuntu-latest`)\n- Python version: 3.12.x\n- Commit/Version: `test` branch around `9424da7` (pre-fix behavior)\n\n## Additional Context\n\n- Affected areas:\n  - `neurons/validator.py` (`store_or_use_cached_evaluation`)\n  - `gittensor/utils/github_api_tools.py` (`load_miners_prs`)\n- Impact:\n  - Can reward stale work\n  - Can distort fairness/incentive accuracy for miners with no current PRs\n",
  "merged_at": "2026-04-17T23:01:28.000Z",
